d to create perfect humans. As a mother and a disability advocate, she shines a light on ableist attitudes, encourages readers to see disability as an aspect of diversity, and marvels at the strange beauty of being human. Her book about raising her daughter is forthcoming from Penguin Press and Piatkus / Little, Brown UK. She writes a related blog&nbsp;<a href=\"https://starinhereye.wordpress.com\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>, and teaches writing at Southern Vermont College.</p>"}],"speaker_name":"Heather Lanier","tags":["children","disability","family","humanity","parenting","personal growth","society","love"],"title":"\"Good\" and \"bad\" are incomplete stories we tell ourselves","video_type":{"id":"4","name":"TED Institute Talk"},"viewed_count":1690207}]}
